headline: S&P 500 Stock Carnival Surfs Higher On Earnings, Israel-Iran Hopes
summary: S&P 500 stock Carnival, already riding high as travel stocks rebound on hopes of an Israel-Iran ceasefire, powered higher after cruising past fiscal second-quarter earnings estimates. CCL, other cruise lines and airline stocks, including United Airlines, gapped higher early Tuesday.

headline: Will Delta Air Lines and United Airlines Make Warren Buffett Eat His Words?
summary: Warren Buffett has criticized the airline industry.  Delta Air Lines and United Airlines are leading a new era of profitability among network carriers.  Warren Buffett has made some critical comments on the airline industry over the last few decades, and frankly, he has a point.
